        <briefdescription>
<para>Select the best slot to boot. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Priority:<orderedlist>
<listitem><para>TESTING slot (continue testing a new image)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>NEW slot (first boot of a new image — marks as TESTING)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>CONFIRMED slot with highest version</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Any CONFIRMED slot</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
<para>If a TESTING slot failed (called with rollback=true), it&apos;s marked INVALID and the other CONFIRMED slot is selected.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>mgr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Boot manager. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>rollback</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>true if the previous boot was unhealthy (trigger rollback). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Slot index (SYN_FW_SLOT_A or SYN_FW_SLOT_B), or SYN_FW_SLOT_NONE. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
